    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4180.0,
      "end_time": 6020.0,
      "text": "Hi, I'm Stephan Schmid."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6020.0,
      "end_time": 9140.0,
      "text": "I'm teaching at the Humboldt\nUniversity in Berlin in Germany,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9140.0,
      "end_time": 11020.0,
      "text": "and today, I want to talk about"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11020.0,
      "end_time": 13699.0,
      "text": "Descartes's famous cogito argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13699.0,
      "end_time": 15740.0,
      "text": "Even if you have never heard of the name"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 15740.0,
      "end_time": 18180.0,
      "text": "\"cogito argument\" before, or of Descartes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 18180.0,
      "end_time": 20660.0,
      "text": "you might have encountered\nthe argument itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20660.0,
      "end_time": 23940.0,
      "text": "It is nothing other than the\nfamous philosophical insight"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 23940.0,
      "end_time": 26140.0,
      "text": "\"I think, therefore, I am,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 26140.0,
      "end_time": 28825.0,
      "text": "or in Latin, \"cogito ergo sum.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29595.0,
      "end_time": 32099.0,
      "text": "This argument has become so popular"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32098.999999999996,
      "end_time": 34780.0,
      "text": "that it has even become\nthe subject of jokes."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 34780.0,
      "end_time": 35780.0,
      "text": "Consider this one."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 35780.0,
      "end_time": 38140.0,
      "text": "Descartes walks into a bar."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 38140.0,
      "end_time": 40220.0,
      "text": "The bartender walks up to him and says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 40220.0,
      "end_time": 41940.0,
      "text": "\"Hey, would you care for a drink?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 41940.0,
      "end_time": 46340.0,
      "text": "Descartes replies, \"Hmm, I think not.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 46605.0,
      "end_time": 48575.0,
      "text": "And poof!"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 48575.0,
      "end_time": 50100.0,
      "text": "He disappears."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 50100.0,
      "end_time": 52900.0,
      "text": "Now, I admit that this\njoke is probably not"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 52900.0,
      "end_time": 55260.0,
      "text": "the best joke ever, but\nDescartes's cogito argument,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 55260.0,
      "end_time": 58860.0,
      "text": "to which this joke appeals,\nis definitely pretty cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 58860.0,
      "end_time": 61780.0,
      "text": "The most exciting feature of\nDescartes's cogito argument"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 61780.0,
      "end_time": 63660.0,
      "text": "is not the argument itself, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 63660.0,
      "end_time": 65379.0,
      "text": "It can actually already be found"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 65379.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67995.0,
      "text": "in Aristotle and Saint Augustine."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 67995.0,
      "end_time": 71140.0,
      "text": "It is rather the philosophical\nquestion that Descartes"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 71140.0,
      "end_time": 72361.0,
      "text": "tried to answer with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 72361.0,
      "end_time": 74700.0,
      "text": "But who was this guy Descartes, anyway?"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 74700.0,
      "end_time": 77380.0,
      "text": "And what is this question\nthat the cogito argument"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 77380.0,
      "end_time": 79060.0,
      "text": "is supposed to answer?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 79060.0,
      "end_time": 82780.0,
      "text": "Rene Descartes was a French\nphilosopher of the seventeenth century."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 82780.0,
      "end_time": 85820.0,
      "text": "He was dissatisfied with\nthe philosophy of his time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 85820.0,
      "end_time": 88712.0,
      "text": "which was dominated by\nscholastic philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 88712.0,
      "end_time": 91700.0,
      "text": "The scholastics saw to\nanswer highly abstract"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 91700.0,
      "end_time": 94060.0,
      "text": "philosophical questions\nmainly on the basis"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 94060.0,
      "end_time": 95860.0,
      "text": "of Aristotle's teaching."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 95860.0,
      "end_time": 98940.0,
      "text": "Descartes was dissatisfied\nwith this kind of philosophy"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 98940.0,
      "end_time": 102020.0,
      "text": "because he considered their\nhighly abstract disputes"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 102020.0,
      "end_time": 105020.0,
      "text": "pointless and futile, and\nalso unable to accommodate"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 105020.0,
      "end_time": 107395.0,
      "text": "the results of the rising\nmechanistic physics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 107395.0,
      "end_time": 110020.0,
      "text": "which sought to account\nfor natural phenomena"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 110020.0,
      "end_time": 111700.0,
      "text": "in mathematical terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 111700.0,
      "end_time": 114760.0,
      "text": "On account of his dissatisfaction\nwith the philosophy of his day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 114760.0,
      "end_time": 116220.0,
      "text": "Descartes came to think"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 116220.0,
      "end_time": 119498.0,
      "text": "that the philosophy was in\nneed of a fundamental reboot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 119498.0,
      "end_time": 121180.0,
      "text": "a completely fresh start."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 121180.0,
      "end_time": 122900.0,
      "text": "This is surely a nice idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 122900.0,
      "end_time": 125220.0,
      "text": "but how do you build a\nnew philosophical system?"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 125220.0,
      "end_time": 128346.0,
      "text": "Well, maybe it's just in\na way we usually build"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 128346.0,
      "end_time": 131100.0,
      "text": "new and stable things, such\nas houses and monuments:"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 131100.0,
      "end_time": 134927.0,
      "text": "just by building them up on a\nstrong and stable foundation."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 134927.0,
      "end_time": 138220.0,
      "text": "Yet, what would serve as an\nappropriate firm foundation"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 138220.0,
      "end_time": 141247.0,
      "text": "upon which to build a\nnew philosophical theory?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 141247.0,
      "end_time": 143893.0,
      "text": "Descartes was convinced that\nnothing could do the job"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 143893.0,
      "end_time": 146220.0,
      "text": "better than our most certain beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 146220.0,
      "end_time": 150078.0,
      "text": "that is, the things that we\ncan really be sure are true."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 150078.0,
      "end_time": 152500.0,
      "text": "Let us now finally turn\nto Descartes's attempt"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 152500.0,
      "end_time": 155543.0,
      "text": "to establish a firm foundation\nfor his new philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 155543.0,
      "end_time": 157820.0,
      "text": "He carries out his attempt\nmost extensively"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 157820.0,
      "end_time": 160429.0,
      "text": "in his \"Meditations On First Philosophy.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 160429.0,
      "end_time": 163380.0,
      "text": "As we said, he wants to\nfind absolutely certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 163380.0,
      "end_time": 165660.0,
      "text": "and unshakable beliefs that he can build"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 165660.0,
      "end_time": 167380.0,
      "text": "his new philosophy upon."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 167380.0,
      "end_time": 169620.0,
      "text": "The method that Descartes suggests"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 169620.0,
      "end_time": 173180.0,
      "text": "has become known as\n\"Descartes' radical doubt.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 173180.0,
      "end_time": 176660.0,
      "text": "The main idea is to\nsubject all our beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 176660.0,
      "end_time": 179509.0,
      "text": "to radical doubt, and\nthen see which of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 179509.0,
      "end_time": 182435.0,
      "text": "can withstand such doubt\nand hence be accepted"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 182435.0,
      "end_time": 184260.0,
      "text": "as absolutely certain."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 184260.0,
      "end_time": 186540.0,
      "text": "As the application of this method reveals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 186540.0,
      "end_time": 188980.0,
      "text": "there is indeed a huge\ndifference between the things"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 188980.0,
      "end_time": 192580.0,
      "text": "that we in fact take\nourselves to be certain about"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 192580.0,
      "end_time": 195860.0,
      "text": "and the things we may justifiably do so."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 196952.0,
      "end_time": 199180.0,
      "text": "Just consider the following examples."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 199180.0,
      "end_time": 201140.0,
      "text": "You're doubtlessly pretty certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 201140.0,
      "end_time": 203309.0,
      "text": "that you're watching a video right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 203309.0,
      "end_time": 206140.0,
      "text": "or that you have brushed\nyour teeth this morning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 206140.0,
      "end_time": 208420.0,
      "text": "or that two plus two equals four."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 208420.0,
      "end_time": 212632.0,
      "text": "Yet are you really justified\nin being so certain?"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 212632.0,
      "end_time": 216020.0,
      "text": "Descartes thinks that after\nhaving employed his method"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 216020.0,
      "end_time": 219380.0,
      "text": "of radical doubt, you will\nhave to admit that you are not."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 219380.0,
      "end_time": 222127.0,
      "text": "Indeed, there are only very few beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 222127.0,
      "end_time": 225490.0,
      "text": "that pass Descartes's\ntest of radical doubt."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 225490.0,
      "end_time": 227109.0,
      "text": "Can you be really certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 227109.0,
      "end_time": 229026.0,
      "text": "that you are watching a video right now?"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 229026.0,
      "end_time": 230420.0,
      "text": "No, you cannot."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 230420.0,
      "end_time": 233952.0,
      "text": "After all you could just\nas well be dreaming."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 233952.0,
      "end_time": 235900.0,
      "text": "The same holds about your beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 235900.0,
      "end_time": 238543.0,
      "text": "that you brushed your teeth this morning."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 238543.0,
      "end_time": 241780.0,
      "text": "And most shockingly, perhaps,\nnot even mathematical beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 241780.0,
      "end_time": 244053.0,
      "text": "escape Descartes's radical doubt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 244053.0,
      "end_time": 246660.0,
      "text": "for how can we be sure that two plus two"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 246660.0,
      "end_time": 248183.0,
      "text": "equals four, say?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 248183.0,
      "end_time": 250684.0,
      "text": "True, we have often convinced ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 250684.0,
      "end_time": 253140.0,
      "text": "that we get a collection of four objects"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 253140.0,
      "end_time": 255939.0,
      "text": "if we unite two collections\nof two objects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 255939.0,
      "end_time": 259084.0,
      "text": "but what ensures that we\ndid not err every time"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 259084.0,
      "end_time": 261755.0,
      "text": "we convinced ourselves of this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 261755.0,
      "end_time": 265140.0,
      "text": "Perhaps there is an evil demon,\nor a wicked neuroscientist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 265140.0,
      "end_time": 267700.0,
      "text": "who constantly manipulates our thoughts"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 267700.0,
      "end_time": 271158.0,
      "text": "by systematically distracting\nus when we try to verify"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 271158.0,
      "end_time": 273540.0,
      "text": "our mathematical beliefs."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 273554.0,
      "end_time": 275631.0,
      "text": "As these considerations show,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 275631.0,
      "end_time": 277140.0,
      "text": "Descartes's method of radical doubt"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 277140.0,
      "end_time": 279160.0,
      "text": "leaves hardly any belief unaffected."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 279160.0,
      "end_time": 280810.0,
      "text": "But there is hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 280810.0,
      "end_time": 283620.0,
      "text": "Descartes argues that\nthere is at least one thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 283620.0,
      "end_time": 285860.0,
      "text": "that we cannot doubt and which we can be"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 285860.0,
      "end_time": 287500.0,
      "text": "absolutely certain about."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 287500.0,
      "end_time": 290140.0,
      "text": "This is the fact that when we doubt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 290140.0,
      "end_time": 293060.0,
      "text": "we cannot doubt that we doubt or think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 293060.0,
      "end_time": 295100.0,
      "text": "for doubting is just a form of thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 296069.0,
      "end_time": 298340.0,
      "text": "But when we can be sure that we think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 298340.0,
      "end_time": 301943.0,
      "text": "we can be equally sure that\nwe exist while we are thinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 301943.0,
      "end_time": 304580.0,
      "text": "for if indeed we can be\nsure that we are thinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 304580.0,
      "end_time": 307100.0,
      "text": "there has to be something\nthat does the thinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 307100.0,
      "end_time": 310349.0,
      "text": "and we are the something, you and I."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 310349.0,
      "end_time": 312260.0,
      "text": "It is, hence, here that we finally arrive"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 312260.0,
      "end_time": 314620.0,
      "text": "at Descartes' famous cogito argument,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 314620.0,
      "end_time": 317124.0,
      "text": "\"I think, therefore, I am.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 318416.0,
      "end_time": 321380.0,
      "text": "The cogito argument then\nassures us of the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 321380.0,
      "end_time": 323364.0,
      "text": "that there is at least one thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 323364.0,
      "end_time": 325100.0,
      "text": "that is impossible to doubt"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 325100.0,
      "end_time": 327780.0,
      "text": "and is thus absolutely certain."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 327780.0,
      "end_time": 330620.0,
      "text": "This is the fact that\nwe exist while we think."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 330620.0,
      "end_time": 332940.0,
      "text": "And this is precisely\nthe unquestionable fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 332940.0,
      "end_time": 336460.0,
      "text": "that can figure as the\nunshakable and firm foundation"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 336460.0,
      "end_time": 338180.0,
      "text": "which Descartes has been looking for"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 338180.0,
      "end_time": 341278.0,
      "text": "in order to build his new\nphilosophical system upon."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 342031.0,
      "end_time": 344416.0,
      "text": "The prospect of building\na whole world view"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 344416.0,
      "end_time": 347103.0,
      "text": "upon the certainly that\nwe exist while we think"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 347103.0,
      "end_time": 349807.0,
      "text": "must strike you as not very promising."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 349807.0,
      "end_time": 352340.0,
      "text": "Given that we can only\nbe certain that we exist"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 352340.0,
      "end_time": 355573.0,
      "text": "while we think, how can\nwe ever know, as we seem to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 355573.0,
      "end_time": 358140.0,
      "text": "that we live on a planet\nwe share with human beings"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 358140.0,
      "end_time": 360856.0,
      "text": "and other animals and\nwhich orbits the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 360856.0,
      "end_time": 363260.0,
      "text": "And how can you know that\ntwo plus two equals four,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 363260.0,
      "end_time": 365749.0,
      "text": "or that you are watching a video?"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 365749.0,
      "end_time": 369152.0,
      "text": "It is indeed a long road\nfor Descartes to restore"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 369152.0,
      "end_time": 371573.0,
      "text": "our certainly in our common sense beliefs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 371573.0,
      "end_time": 375573.0,
      "text": "and many of these beliefs have\nto be abandoned along the way."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 375573.0,
      "end_time": 379176.0,
      "text": "Amongst those are our\ncommonly accepted beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 379176.0,
      "end_time": 381620.0,
      "text": "that materials things are really colored"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 381620.0,
      "end_time": 384776.0,
      "text": "or have other sensory\nproperties like tastes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 384776.0,
      "end_time": 386838.0,
      "text": "smells, and sounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 386838.0,
      "end_time": 390309.0,
      "text": "It takes Descartes the whole\nrest of his six meditations"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 390309.0,
      "end_time": 393260.0,
      "text": "to walk down this road\nand restore our confidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 393260.0,
      "end_time": 395620.0,
      "text": "in our beliefs of mathematical truths"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 395620.0,
      "end_time": 398020.0,
      "text": "and the existence of the outer world."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 398020.0,
      "end_time": 402832.0,
      "text": "It would take us hours to\ncarefully reenact all the steps."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 402832.0,
      "end_time": 405460.0,
      "text": "However, in order to get a rough grasp"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 405460.0,
      "end_time": 407900.0,
      "text": "of Descartes's procedure,\nit will be worthwhile"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 407900.0,
      "end_time": 410580.0,
      "text": "to reconstruct just one\nstep that Descartes takes"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 410580.0,
      "end_time": 412500.0,
      "text": "in order to extend the stock of beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 412500.0,
      "end_time": 415705.0,
      "text": "that we can justifiably be certain about."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 415705.0,
      "end_time": 418580.0,
      "text": "The method Descartes employs for extending"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 418580.0,
      "end_time": 421680.0,
      "text": "our certain beliefs\nconsists in squeezing out"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 421680.0,
      "end_time": 424533.0,
      "text": "the certainties he has already arrived at."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 424533.0,
      "end_time": 427444.0,
      "text": "Actually, we have already\nencountered this method,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 427444.0,
      "end_time": 429820.0,
      "text": "for Descartes's cogito\nargument is such a way"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 429820.0,
      "end_time": 433660.0,
      "text": "of squeezing out a certain\nbelief or idea from another."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 433660.0,
      "end_time": 436567.0,
      "text": "After all, the cogito\nargument is an argument,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 436567.0,
      "end_time": 438820.0,
      "text": "that is, a transition or an inference"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 438820.0,
      "end_time": 440620.0,
      "text": "from one belief to another."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 441650.0,
      "end_time": 444820.0,
      "text": "The unshakable belief that\nthis argument starts out from"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 444820.0,
      "end_time": 448401.0,
      "text": "is the belief that we are\nthinking when we are doubting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 448401.0,
      "end_time": 451092.0,
      "text": "and we arrive at this\ncertainty just by observing"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 451092.0,
      "end_time": 453540.0,
      "text": "that whatever we might\ndoubt, we cannot doubt"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 453540.0,
      "end_time": 456361.0,
      "text": "that we doubt when we doubt."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 456361.0,
      "end_time": 459340.0,
      "text": "Now, the cogito argument\ntakes this certainty"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 459340.0,
      "end_time": 462660.0,
      "text": "and squeezes out the new\ncertainty that we cannot"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 462660.0,
      "end_time": 464900.0,
      "text": "only be sure that we think when we doubt"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 464900.0,
      "end_time": 468647.0,
      "text": "but also that we exist when we think."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 468647.0,
      "end_time": 471340.0,
      "text": "And it is exactly this\nnewly gained certainty"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 471340.0,
      "end_time": 474180.0,
      "text": "of our existence which the\ncogito argument provides us"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 474180.0,
      "end_time": 476660.0,
      "text": "that Descartes squeezes next."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 476660.0,
      "end_time": 480370.0,
      "text": "In a famous passage of his\nsecond meditation, he writes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 481262.0,
      "end_time": 484860.0,
      "text": "\"I am, I exist - that is certain."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 484860.0,
      "end_time": 486300.0,
      "text": "\"But for how long?"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 486300.0,
      "end_time": 488540.0,
      "text": "\"For as long as I am thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 488540.0,
      "end_time": 491100.0,
      "text": "\"I am, then, in the strict sense only a thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 491100.0,
      "end_time": 494860.0,
      "text": "\"that thinks; that is, I\nam a mind, or intelligence"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 494860.0,
      "end_time": 497020.0,
      "text": "\"or intellect or reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 497020.0,
      "end_time": 500170.0,
      "text": "\"But for all that, I am\na thing which is real"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 500170.0,
      "end_time": 501640.0,
      "text": "\"and which truly exists."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 501640.0,
      "end_time": 503780.0,
      "text": "\"But what kind of a thing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 503780.0,
      "end_time": 507546.0,
      "text": "\"As I have just said - a thinking thing.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 507546.0,
      "end_time": 510800.0,
      "text": "As becomes plain here, Descartes\nimmediately squeezes out"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 510800.0,
      "end_time": 513140.0,
      "text": "further information about his nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 513140.0,
      "end_time": 516219.0,
      "text": "from the certain belief that\nhe exists while he thinks."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 517403.0,
      "end_time": 520620.0,
      "text": "As a result, Descartes cannot\nonly know with certainty"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 520620.0,
      "end_time": 523460.0,
      "text": "that he exists, but also\nthat he is a thinking thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 523460.00000000006,
      "end_time": 525380.0,
      "text": "a thing capable of thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 526180.0,
      "end_time": 528625.0,
      "text": "This is still not a lot, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 528625.0,
      "end_time": 531860.0,
      "text": "At this stage, Descartes can\nonly be ensured of the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 531860.0,
      "end_time": 533980.0,
      "text": "that he is a thinking thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 533980.0,
      "end_time": 537180.0,
      "text": "and it is still an open question\nwhether he also has a body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 537180.0,
      "end_time": 539573.0,
      "text": "as we usually suppose."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 539573.0,
      "end_time": 542020.0,
      "text": "If you are puzzled now, or even afraid"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 542020.0,
      "end_time": 544580.0,
      "text": "that you cannot know whether\nyou really have a body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 544580.0,
      "end_time": 546340.0,
      "text": "that you really are watching this video,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 546340.0,
      "end_time": 549284.0,
      "text": "or that you really have brushed\nyour teeth this morning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 549284.0,
      "end_time": 551020.0,
      "text": "the only comfort I can give you"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 551020.0,
      "end_time": 554260.0,
      "text": "is that Descartes at least\nthought that it can be proved"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 554260.0,
      "end_time": 556460.0,
      "text": "that we can be certain that we have a body"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 556460.0,
      "end_time": 558940.0,
      "text": "and that our senses, by\nand large, assure us"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 558940.0,
      "end_time": 561866.0,
      "text": "of the existence of other\ncorporeal things, even"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 561866.0,
      "end_time": 565749.0,
      "text": "though they systematically\ndeceive us about their nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 565749.0,
      "end_time": 569180.0,
      "text": "And this can be proved by further\nsqueezing out our clear"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 569180.0,
      "end_time": 572460.0,
      "text": "and distinct idea of\nourselves as a thinking thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 573475.0,
      "end_time": 576060.0,
      "text": "If this promise is not\nenough to give you comfort,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 576060.0,
      "end_time": 579300.0,
      "text": "then there is only one\nlast advice I can give you."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 579300.0,
      "end_time": 580980.0,
      "text": "Go and get a copy of Descartes's"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 580980.0,
      "end_time": 582780.0,
      "text": "\"Meditations On First Philosophy,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 582780.0,
      "end_time": 585469.0,
      "text": "and start reading his third meditation."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 593080.0,
      "end_time": 596080.0,
      "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community"
    }
  ]
}